#15164
{DThe Towermaster's Private Chambers{X~
This chamber manages to be both stately and luxuriant at the same time. 
Black velvet drapes hang from every wall, reflecting a cold light from a
number of large candles in iron sconces.  A carved four-poster bed sits
against the back wall next to a towering bookshelf overflowing with various
tomes.  An overstuffed couch lies against the south wall, with an equally
stuffed chair and polished writing desk near the hearth on the opposite
side.  Columns of polished ebony line the hearth to either side, supporting
a black marble mantle above the magical flame.  High above in the vaulted
ceiling, a large circular window opens to the sky above; admitting both the
sunshine and the shadowy light of Nuitari at High Sanction.  
~
